    "description": {
      "value": "<p>As an action, you can make a melee spell attack using your augment attack modifier (see <strong>Augment Effects</strong>) against a creature or item within reach. On a successful hit, the target becomes cursed so that it is vulnerable to all damage. If the target is a creature, it can attempt a CON save against your augment save DC (see <strong>Augment Effects</strong>) each time it takes a new instance of damage, ending the curse on a success. Once you use this feature, you must finish a long rest before you can use it again.</p>",
